2026-04-14: Result card redesigned: age in words, date in long format, confidence as pill (sentence case, not uppercase), ATS badge, collapsible evidence.
2026-04-14: Replaced the old first-hit detector with a typed evidence engine that collects all candidate dates, chooses the oldest credible posted date, and exposes comparison evidence through `all_dates`.
2026-04-14: Expanded generic backend extraction to include page metadata/regex, Open Graph, embedded JSON payloads, Jina render fallback, sitemap `lastmod`, and Wayback archive ceilings.
2026-04-14: Added SmartRecruiters as a direct ATS API fallback in the new engine; broader platform detection now explicitly marks Indeed and LinkedIn as blocked and Google Careers as unsupported for dates.
2026-04-14: Broke backward compatibility on the API response intentionally because the product is not yet in production; the richer contract is now the source of truth and clients should adapt to it.
2026-04-14: Chose not to invent unsupported ATS endpoints; direct fallbacks should only be added when the signal is verified from real payloads or stable public feeds.
2026-04-14: Added explicit parity-hardening coverage for repost conflicts and hidden metadata extraction before extending more ATS handlers.
2026-04-14: Added Rippling support only after verifying a real public signal on live pages: `__NEXT_DATA__ -> props.pageProps.apiData.jobPost.createdOn`. Kept this as a platform-specific handler instead of broad generic `__NEXT_DATA__` walking to avoid noisy title/company extraction from large Next.js payloads.
2026-04-14: Added iCIMS support by deriving the internal API host from `<base href>` and querying `/api/jobs`, because the visible public host often does not serve the JSON feed directly. Matching uses `req_id`, `slug`, and `apply_url`, with `posted_date` treated as durable and `update_date` as refresh evidence.
2026-04-14: Added Dover support only after verifying the live public endpoint `GET /api/v1/inbound/application-portal-job/{jobId}` on `app.dover.com`. Use `created` as the durable posted date and keep location/compensation metadata as hidden insights.
2026-04-14: Downgraded generic `createdAt` extraction from high-confidence to low-confidence after a live iCIMS false positive. ATS handlers now override weaker generic title/company/location values when they have platform-native data.
40: 2026-04-14: Fully redesigned frontend ResultCard to consume the richer backend schema. Added distinct UI for non-success statuses (blocked/amber, unsupported/neutral, no_date/info). Surfaces title/company/location/employment_type, repost banner, summary, chosen source with reliability dot, collapsible hidden insights, and warnings. Used inline SVGs to avoid new dependencies.
41: 2026-04-14: Added SmartRecruiters to platform carousel with red/pink gel button gradient. Updated placeholder URL rotation to include SmartRecruiters examples.
2026-04-14: Removed an accidental nested git repo inside `site/` so the frontend can be tracked from the main repository as a normal monorepo directory.
2026-04-14: Expanded the root `.gitignore` for monorepo hygiene to ignore frontend install/build artifacts (`node_modules`, `.next`, `.vercel`, logs, build outputs) while allowing the `site/` source and lockfile to be committed.
2026-04-14: Replaced the boilerplate `site/README.md` with a repo-specific note and removed a mount-only React effect in `PlatformCarousel` so frontend lint passes cleanly.
2026-04-14: Added Workable as a direct ATS fallback using the embedded `window.jobBoard.initialState` payload, keyed on `shortcode` / `id` match and preferring platform-native title/company/location/employment over weaker generic page-shell fields. Added `created` as the durable posted date and `updated` as refresh evidence with a note that it reflects freshness, not original posting time.
2026-04-14: Introduced a `PLATFORM_CAPABILITIES` registry and `/api/v1/platforms` endpoint so backend support (direct vs generic vs blocked vs unsupported) is a first-class, testable contract instead of README prose. Added Dover to the registry because it already had a direct handler. Unknown platforms default to `generic` supported with empty detection hints.
2026-04-14: Promoted Workday to a direct handler after verifying the public CXS endpoint live (`GET /wday/cxs/{tenant}/{site}/job/{jobPath}` → `jobPostingInfo.startDate`). Extended `detect_platform` to capture `site` and `job_path` into `URLMetadata.extra` so the fallback can build the CXS URL without re-parsing.
2026-04-14: Promoted Oracle HCM to a direct handler after verifying the public REST endpoint live (`GET /hcmRestApi/resources/latest/recruitingCEJobRequisitionDetails?finder=ById;Id="{reqId}",siteNumber={site}` → `items[0].ExternalPostedStartDate`). `detect_platform` now extracts the `sites/{site}` segment and requisition id into `URLMetadata`.
2026-04-14: Left Jobvite, BambooHR, SuccessFactors, ADP, Brassring, Paycor, and Avature as detection-only generic platforms because live probing did not surface a stable public payload. Enforced the repo rule to avoid inventing endpoints; these platforms continue to rely on JSON-LD / metadata / Jina render / sitemap / Wayback signals.
2026-04-14: Promoted BambooHR to a direct handler after verifying the public `GET https://{company}.bamboohr.com/careers/{jobId}/detail` endpoint on a live board (`signal1.bamboohr.com/careers/39/detail` → `result.jobOpening.datePosted`). `detect_platform` now captures the company subdomain and job id from `/careers/{jobId}` URLs.
2026-04-14: Promoted Jobvite to a direct handler after verifying the public XML feed `GET https://jobs.jobvite.com/CompanyJobs/Xml.aspx?c={companyEId}&j={jobId}` on a live board (`clinch/job/oD2D4fw6` → `<date>10/5/2017</date>`). The handler scrapes `companyEId` from the public page config when it is not already present in the URL, and `detect_platform` now parses both modern `/company/job/{jobId}` and legacy querystring feed URLs.
2026-04-14: Promoted Brassring to a direct handler after verifying that live public job pages expose durable `DC.Date` metadata on the job-details HTML (`HomeWithPreLoad?...jobid=...&partnerid=...&siteid=...`). The handler also parses `og:title` to recover title/company when the generic page shell is noisy.
2026-04-14: Promoted SuccessFactors to a direct handler using page fingerprints (`j2w.init`, `rmkcdn.successfactors.com`, `ssoCompanyId`) plus the public RSS feed shape `/services/rss/job/?locale={locale}&keywords={slug}`. Added a durable fallback for the common `<meta itemprop="datePosted">` pattern because some boards expose the date directly on the HTML.
2026-04-14: Promoted Avature to a direct handler after verifying live portal feeds and sitemaps on `bloomberg.avature.net`: `/{portal}/SearchJobs/feed/` exposes job `pubDate` and `/{portal}/sitemap_index.xml` chains to portal-specific sitemaps. The handler treats feed `pubDate` as the durable posting signal and sitemap `lastmod` as lower-confidence freshness evidence.
2026-04-14: Did not promote ADP yet even though the public requisition endpoint exists (`/careercenter/public/events/staffing/v1/job-requisitions/{jobId}?cid={cid}&ccId={ccId}`), because the live sample probed returned a sparse payload without `postDate`, title, or location fields. Keep ADP generic until a second verified sample confirms the durable field mapping.
2026-04-14: Promoted Gem to a direct handler after verifying Gem's documented public Job Board API live (`GET https://api.gem.com/job_board/v0/{board}/job_posts/`). Prefer `first_published_at` as the durable posted date, keep `updated_at` as refresh evidence, and only fall back to `created_at` when `first_published_at` is missing.
2026-04-14: Added `.tmp/` to `.gitignore` because competitor bundle dumps and other reverse-engineering scratch files are useful during investigation but should not become tracked repo state.
2026-04-14: Promoted Recruitee to a direct handler after verifying the public `GET https://{company}.recruitee.com/api/offers/{slug}` endpoint. Prefer `published_at`, treat `updated_at` as refresh evidence, and only fall back to `created_at` when `published_at` is missing.
2026-04-14: Promoted Breezy HR to a direct handler by parsing the public `data-position` payload embedded on job pages. Prefer `first_publish_date`, treat `last_publish_date` as refresh evidence, and keep department/category metadata as hidden insights.
2026-04-14: Added direct platform support for Teamtailor, Personio, and JazzHR / applytojob based on live public page signals rather than private APIs: Teamtailor via `article:published_time` + JSON-LD, Personio via page JobPosting schema plus `/xml?language=...` fallback, and JazzHR via public JobPosting JSON-LD on detail pages.
2026-04-14: Collapsed employer-specific URL patterns out of the platform taxonomy. Stripe now resolves into `greenhouse`, Goldman Sachs resolves into `oracle_hcm`, and employer-only public backends like Amazon/Bending Spoons resolve into a generic `custom_backend` platform instead of surfacing employer names as first-class platforms.
2026-04-14: Repaired website deployment drift by connecting Vercel project `jobcarbon-web` to `https://github.com/dhiyaancnirmal/jobcarbon.git` from the `site/` root, then promoting a fresh production deployment from the clean committed tree. The outage was stale frontend aliasing, not backend/API failure.
2026-04-14: Git auto-deploys initially still failed because the Vercel project `rootDirectory` was unset (`null`) after Git connection, so Git builds ran from the repo root and could not find a Next `app/` directory. Patched the project via the Vercel API to `rootDirectory = "site"` and redeployed production successfully.
2026-04-14: Fixed same-day age labels in the website by computing relative age from `likely_posted_date` on the client in the browser's local calendar date. The backend's `likely_age_days` is UTC-based and can be off by one near midnight for US users.
2026-04-14: Fixed Ashby posting-date selection for timezone edges by normalizing `ashby.api.publishedAt` into the board's declared timezone (`timezone` in the page payload) before comparing it to date-only JSON-LD and regex matches. This resolves cases where a UTC timestamp after midnight should still count as the previous local posting date.
64: 2026-04-14: Expanded frontend platform carousel from 4 to 28 platforms with unique brand-color gel button gradients for each. Added PlatformCapability type and fetchPlatforms() to api.ts for the new /api/v1/platforms endpoint. Updated placeholder URL rotation to cover 10 major ATS platforms. Carousel scroll duration doubled to 40s for the larger item set. Removed withLogos prop from PlatformCarousel since all platforms now use text-only gel buttons.
2026-04-14: Refactored frontend to support competitor-parity history view. Extracted ResultCard, added SearchHistory, HistoryCard, ConfirmModal, and PlatformDialog components. Built frontend API pass-through for anonymous session storage via HttpOnly cookies so that tracking remains completely invisible to client-side inspection. Added pre-submit platform intercepts for blocked/unsupported platforms.
2026-04-14: Re-styled the empty state icon in the search history to use the gel aesthetic (box shadows, inset highlights, gradient) and updated the empty state copy to be more concise and drop mention of URLs and anonymity.
2026-04-14: Fixed carousel/history visibility: PlatformCarousel now shows for new users (history empty), SearchHistory only appears after first search. Removed the empty-state "workspace" card since it should never display before the user has interacted. Cleared all "workspace" branding language.
2026-04-14: Tuned frontend vertical spacing by reducing gap classes in page.tsx (gap-12 to gap-6) and job-checker.tsx (gap-10 to gap-6).
2026-04-14: Adjusted PlatformCarousel width using negative margins (-mx-3 and sm:-mx-6) to physically stretch the container. This visually aligns the unmasked center track with the search input boundaries, compensating for the CSS linear-gradient mask effect.
2026-04-14: Removed "Collapse" button from expanded HistoryCard. Users can collapse items by toggling them or expanding other cards. Fixed state logic causing infinite loop default expansions.
2026-04-14: Implemented anonymous history persistence in `jobcarbon_api.py` using stdlib SQLite (`JOBCARBON_DB_PATH`, default `.tmp/jobcarbon.db`) with `anonymous_sessions` and `search_history` tables plus `session_id, created_at DESC` index; no ORM or third-party deps added.
2026-04-14: Added secure anonymous session middleware for `/api/v1/history*` routes using `jobcarbon_session` HttpOnly cookie (Secure, SameSite=None, Path=/, Max-Age 30 days). Only hashed cookie tokens are stored server-side; invalid/missing cookie on GET returns empty history, POST creates a new session.
2026-04-14: Added backend history endpoints to `jobcarbon_api`: `GET /api/v1/history`, `POST /api/v1/history`, `DELETE /api/v1/history`, and `DELETE /api/v1/history/{id}` with idempotent deletes and session-scoped isolation.
2026-04-14: Reworked API CORS to strict origin allowlist (`JOBCARBON_ALLOWED_ORIGINS`, default localhost + production domains), enabled credentialed CORS (`Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true`), expanded allowed methods to include DELETE, and block disallowed origins with explicit 403.
2026-04-14: Updated frontend history fetches in `site/src/lib/api.ts` to use `credentials: include` so HttpOnly session cookies are sent/received for history persistence.
2026-04-14: Expanded `tests/test_jobcarbon_api.py` to cover session cookie issuance, history CRUD, cross-session isolation, payload validation, and credentialed CORS behavior. Full suite now passes (`python3 -m unittest discover -s tests -v`, 60 tests).
2026-04-14: Reverted frontend search-history UI per user request — they strongly disliked the filter bar replacing the carousel and asked to restore the simpler layout from commit 5425a2c. Restored `site/src/app/page.tsx`, `site/src/app/globals.css`, `site/src/components/job-checker.tsx`, `site/src/components/platform-carousel.tsx`, `site/src/lib/api.ts` to HEAD and deleted uncommitted `confirm-modal.tsx`, `history-card.tsx`, `platform-dialog.tsx`, `result-card.tsx`, `search-history.tsx`, `lib/platforms.ts`. Backend history endpoints left untouched.
2026-04-14: Re-applied the tighter main vertical spacing in `site/src/app/page.tsx` (main `gap-12` → `gap-6`). User previously compressed this and considers the committed `gap-12` too airy above and below the URL input.
2026-04-14: Moved the `23+ platforms supported` label + `PlatformCarousel` from `page.tsx` into `JobChecker` and gated it on `state.status !== "success"`, so the carousel disappears once a result is loaded (it's noise once the user has what they came for). Reappears on error/idle/loading.
2026-04-14: Added `unicode-animations` (npm, 1 dep, 82.7 kB) and created `site/src/components/spinner.tsx` — a small client component that cycles braille frames from the package. Used the `scan` preset (10 frames, 70ms) in two places: inside the gel Check button while submitting, and in a centered loading card that replaces the carousel during the request. User explicitly asked for a nice loading animation instead of live progress steps; dark mode was explicitly declined.
2026-04-14: Rebuilt frontend search-history UX from scratch after user's revert-anger incident: `confirm-modal.tsx`, `platform-dialog.tsx`, `result-card.tsx`, `history-card.tsx`, `search-history.tsx`, `lib/platforms.ts`. The earlier revert deleted these uncommitted files; rebuild uses `localStorage` (`jobcarbon_history_v1`) instead of the backend cookie API so it matches the "No cookies · History stored locally" microcopy. Flow: submit → `addHistoryItem(url, result)` → newest entry expanded by default; filter bar searches title/company/platform/url; per-card Recheck/Remove; Clear-all gated by `ConfirmModal`; `PlatformDialog` intercepts LinkedIn/Indeed/Google/ClearCompany/YC pre-submit.
2026-04-14: Fixed `<details>` reflow-bug: removed `justify-center`/`flex-1` from `<main>` and switched to top-anchored padding `pt-[calc(50vh-7.125rem)]` where 7.125rem ≈ half of idle content height (228px/2). Pixel-verified via agent-browser getBoundingClientRect: content center 316.69 vs viewport center 316.50 (0.19px off). This keeps the idle layout visually centered but prevents the whole component from shifting upward when dropdowns expand.
2026-04-14: Hardened `ResultCard` with `?.` optional chaining on `warnings`, `all_dates`, `hidden_insights` because legacy/mock history items in localStorage may predate fields added to the backend response schema. Without this, rehydrating an old localStorage entry crashed the page with `Cannot read properties of undefined`.
2026-04-14: Added `/about` page with three sections — How it works (7 sources: ATS API, JSON-LD, metadata/regex, Open Graph, Jina Reader, sitemap, Wayback), Supported platforms (28-row status table), and FAQ (6 items covering ghost jobs, reposts, Indeed/LinkedIn blocking, privacy, accuracy, no-date fallback). Updated `layout.tsx` with OG/Twitter metadata, `metadataBase`, and footer Home · About · v0.2.0.
2026-04-14: Switched browser automation to the local `agent-browser` CLI (`/opt/homebrew/bin/agent-browser`) per explicit user directive "stop fucking using firecrawl." Firecrawl MCP remains installed but must not be called for this project.
2026-04-14: Removed the stale frontend `localStorage` history path and rewired the rebuilt history UI to the existing backend anonymous-session API (`GET/POST/DELETE /api/v1/history` with `credentials: include`). Deleted `site/src/lib/history.ts`, updated homepage/confirm-modal/about copy to describe anonymous server-side history tied to an HttpOnly cookie, and verified the rendered copy on `http://localhost:3000` with `agent-browser`.
2026-04-14: Removed the extra homepage microcopy entirely, replaced the unicode loading animation/card with a minimal three-dot inline spinner in the submit button, and paused the placeholder typing animation whenever the user has entered a URL or a request is loading. Successful submits now leave the typed URL visible in the input instead of clearing it.
2026-04-14: Dropped the `pt-[calc(50vh-7.125rem)]` centering hack on the homepage. The idle view now uses a plain viewport-height main section so the hero and footer are visible without a scrollbar, and the footer no longer renders a top divider line.
2026-04-14: The local `NetworkError` was not caused by unpushed frontend changes. The root cause was that `jobcarbon-site` was running under PM2 while `jobcarbon-api` was not. Started `jobcarbon-api` under PM2 on `127.0.0.1:8000` and changed the frontend dev fallback API base to `http://localhost:8000` when `NEXT_PUBLIC_JOBCARBON_API` is unset.
2026-04-14: Removed the now-unused `unicode-animations` dependency from `site/package.json` after replacing the spinner with CSS-based dots.
2026-04-14: Collapsed the placeholder animation effect dependency to a single boolean (`placeholderAnimationPaused`) and restarted `jobcarbon-site` under PM2 to clear the stale Fast Refresh hook-signature state that was causing the `useEffect changed size between renders` console error.
2026-04-14: Reverted the `/about` redesign experiment after user rejection. Restored the simpler structure: short intro, "How it works" source list, 28-row platform status table, and FAQ cards. Validated with `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, and `agent-browser` on `http://localhost:3000/about`.
